{"id":"pattern-example-001","type":"pattern","fact":"Example: Use mock factories for all test data instead of manual mock objects with 'as Type' assertions.","recommendation":"Create centralized mock factory functions (createMockUser, createMockOrg, etc.) and import them in tests.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"documentation","reference":"Testing guide","date":"2026-01-09"}],"tags":["testing","mocks","factories"],"affectedFiles":["**/*.test.ts"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-01-09T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-01-09T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"pattern-empty-vue-stubs","type":"pattern","fact":"When creating router entries that lazy-load pages not yet implemented, use empty stubs with only <template><div /></template> and no <script> block. Stubs with script code register as 0% coverage.","recommendation":"Create minimal template-only stubs for pages referenced by router but built in later tasks. Replace with full implementation when the task is reached.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #16 coverage gate failure","date":"2026-04-12"}],"tags":["vue","coverage","router","stubs","parallel-tasks"],"affectedFiles":["packages/client/src/pages/**/*.vue"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"pattern-subagent-tdd-incomplete","type":"pattern","fact":"Coding subagents frequently complete only the TDD red phase (test files) before hitting context limits, leaving implementation unwritten.","recommendation":"After subagent completion, always verify both test AND implementation files exist. Be prepared to implement from the test spec when the agent only produced tests.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #17 orchestrated execution — WU-004/005 and WU-006/007 agents","date":"2026-04-12"}],"tags":["orchestration","subagents","tdd","context-limits"],"affectedFiles":[],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"pattern-bookmark-toggle-on-conflict","type":"pattern","fact":"Bookmark toggle uses INSERT ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING RETURNING * to detect existence. When the row already exists, RETURNING produces no rows (null). The route interprets null as 'already existed' and deletes it — a clean toggle without a separate existence check query.","recommendation":"Use this ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING RETURNING * pattern for any idempotent toggle endpoint where you need create-or-remove behavior in a single POST.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #18 Task 3 bookmark routes","date":"2026-04-12"}],"tags":["postgresql","on-conflict","toggle","bookmarks","idempotent"],"affectedFiles":["packages/server/src/db/queries/bookmarks.ts","packages/server/src/routes/bookmarks.ts"],"affectedServices":["createBookmark","bookmarkRoutes"],"createdAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"pattern-parallel-route-registration","type":"pattern","fact":"Multiple parallel coding subagents can each add import + app.register() lines to app.ts without merge conflicts. Fastify route registration is additive and order-independent — route plugins don't depend on each other's registration order.","recommendation":"When decomposing server route work into parallel tasks, let each task add its own app.register() call to app.ts. No coordination needed between tasks.","confidence":"medium","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #18 parallel Tasks 2-4 execution","date":"2026-04-12"}],"tags":["fastify","parallel","subagents","app-registration","orchestration"],"affectedFiles":["packages/server/src/app.ts"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"pattern-worktree-setup-forge-monorepo","type":"pattern","fact":"Git worktrees share only .git/ with the main repo; the new worktree's filesystem starts without node_modules or .env. Running npm, vitest, or the server inside a fresh worktree fails until dependencies are installed AND a .env is provided (the server defaults to PORT=3001 and reads DATABASE_URL from .env at the repo root).","recommendation":"After `git worktree add <path> -b feat/<name> main`, run these three commands in the new worktree before doing any test or server work: (1) `npm install` at the worktree root (the monorepo uses npm workspaces so this resolves all three packages), (2) `cp /path/to/main/repo/.env .env`, (3) if the main worktree already has a dev server on :3001, start the feature server on a different port with `PORT=3002 npx tsx packages/server/src/server.ts` and override baseUrl in Bruno via `--env-var baseUrl=http://localhost:3002`.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #3 orchestration setup","date":"2026-04-13"}],"tags":["git","worktree","monorepo","setup","npm","bruno"],"affectedFiles":[".env",".env.example","package.json"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"pattern-fastify-plugin-auth-dep-001","type":"pattern","fact":"A Fastify plugin whose hooks or decorators call app.authenticate must declare dependencies: [\"auth-plugin\"] in its fp() config, because authenticate is registered as a preHandler decorator by authPlugin and must exist before downstream plugins reference it.","recommendation":"When a plugin registers decorators that reference app.authenticate (e.g., app.aiGate = [app.authenticate, ...]), wrap it with fastify-plugin and set dependencies: [\"auth-plugin\"] to guarantee load ordering.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"self-reflect","reference":"issue #9 LangChain AI autocomplete","date":"2026-04-13"}],"tags":["fastify","plugins","auth","fastify-plugin"],"affectedFiles":["packages/server/src/plugins/**/*.ts"],"affectedServices":["server"],"createdAt":"2026-04-13T22:30:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-13T22:30:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"pattern-abort-handlers-helper-001","type":"pattern","fact":"Fastify light-my-request (app.inject) does not let tests emit close on request.raw mid-stream, so the SSE handler's timeout + disconnect abort branches are unreachable via integration tests.","recommendation":"Extract an exported helper like createAbortHandlers(req, slot, timeoutMs) that installs a setTimeout + request.raw.on(\"close\") and returns a cleanup function. Unit-test it with an EventEmitter as the fake request.raw to reach 100% branch coverage.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"self-reflect","reference":"issue #9 LangChain AI autocomplete","date":"2026-04-13"}],"tags":["fastify","sse","testing","coverage"],"affectedFiles":["packages/server/src/routes/**/*.ts","packages/server/src/__tests__/routes/**/*.ts"],"affectedServices":["server"],"createdAt":"2026-04-13T22:30:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-13T22:30:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"pattern-bruno-assert-syntax","type":"pattern","fact":"Forge's Bruno collection uses declarative 'assert { res.status: eq N }' blocks, matching the existing search/*.bru convention. Chai-style 'tests { expect(res.getStatus()).to.equal(N) }' is also valid Bruno syntax but is NOT the project standard.","recommendation":"New .bru files MUST use the declarative assert{} form for status checks. The CI lint guard accepts either '^assert \\{' or '^tests \\{' at line start so pre-existing Chai blocks still pass, but new contributions should match the project convention.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #28 WU-004 implementation","date":"2026-04-13"}],"tags":["bruno","testing","syntax","convention"],"affectedFiles":["bruno/**/*.bru"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"pattern-bruno-created-vs-fixture-vars","type":"pattern","fact":"When a .bru file creates a new resource (e.g. posts/create-post.bru), its post-response script MUST capture the ID into a created* variable (createdPostId, createdRevisionId), NOT overwrite the fixture variable (postId, revisionId). The fixture variable stays pinned to a seeded UUID so order-independent reads always find a stable target.","recommendation":"Producer .bru: bru.setVar('createdPostId', res.body.post.id). Consumers of the ephemeral post (delete-post, update-post, publish-post) use {{createdPostId}}. Consumers of the fixture (comments, votes, bookmarks, reads) use {{postId}}.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #28 WU-003 variable-lifecycle audit","date":"2026-04-13"}],"tags":["bruno","variables","fixtures","lifecycle","producer-consumer"],"affectedFiles":["bruno/**/*.bru","bruno/environments/*.bru"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"pattern-sse-route-shared-helpers-001","type":"pattern","fact":"packages/server/src/routes/ai.ts exports file-scoped SSE helpers (SSE_HEADERS const, TIMEOUT_MS const, writeEvent function, createAbortHandlers factory). A new SSE endpoint (e.g. /generate added alongside /complete) is added by appending a second app.post() handler in the same file that reuses these exports — no new helpers, no refactor, identical abort/timeout semantics across endpoints.","recommendation":"When adding an SSE endpoint to an existing route file with established helpers, EXTEND the file (append a second handler) rather than creating a parallel route file. Reuse SSE_HEADERS + writeEvent + createAbortHandlers + TIMEOUT_MS verbatim. The finally-block cleanup pattern (`cleanupAborts(); slot.release(); reply.raw.end();`) is the contract every SSE handler in the file must follow.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"self-reflect","reference":"Issue #10 WU-004 route extension","date":"2026-04-14"}],"tags":["fastify","sse","routes","helpers","reuse"],"affectedFiles":["packages/server/src/routes/ai.ts"],"affectedServices":["server"],"createdAt":"2026-04-14T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-14T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"pattern-langchain-runnable-lambda-adapter-001","type":"pattern","fact":"When a LangChain chain input type has OPTIONAL fields (e.g. `language?: string`) but the ChatPromptTemplate references those fields as template variables (e.g. `{language}`), `.format()` requires a string value for every referenced variable — undefined throws 'Missing variable'. Prepending a RunnableLambda in the pipe chain that defaults the optional fields keeps the prompt variable contract stable without forcing callers to provide a default.","recommendation":"Structure the chain as `defaultLambda.pipe(prompt).pipe(model).pipe(parser)` where `defaultLambda = RunnableLambda.from((input) => ({ ...input, language: input.language ?? '' }))`. The lambda is typed explicitly (no `as any`). Verify with two tests (field-omitted vs field-provided) so V8 branch coverage sees both branches of the `??` operator.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"self-reflect","reference":"Issue #10 WU-003 generate chain","date":"2026-04-14"}],"tags":["langchain","runnable","prompt-template","input-adapter","optional-fields"],"affectedFiles":["packages/server/src/plugins/langchain/chains/**/*.ts"],"affectedServices":["server"],"createdAt":"2026-04-14T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-14T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"pattern-ai-acquire-decorator-001","type":"pattern","fact":"When a route needs conditional AI rate limiting (e.g., search is public but AI search needs auth), expose app.aiAcquire(userId): AiSlot | null from the langchain plugin instead of using aiGate as a preHandler. Acquire/release the slot manually in a try/finally block within the route handler.","recommendation":"Use app.aiAcquire() for routes that mix authenticated AI paths with unauthenticated plain paths. Never use aiGate preHandler on mixed routes — it sends 401/429 responses that block the non-AI path.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #11 AI-powered search, WU-004","date":"2026-04-14"}],"tags":["fastify","rate-limiting","ai","langchain"],"affectedFiles":["packages/server/src/plugins/langchain/index.ts","packages/server/src/routes/search.ts"],"affectedServices":["server"],"createdAt":"2026-04-14T15:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-14T15:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"pattern-graceful-ai-fallback-001","type":"pattern","fact":"AI-enhanced endpoints should follow a cascading fallback pattern: try jwtVerify → try aiAcquire → try chain → use filters, with catch → fallback to plain behavior at each step. Users always get results; AI failure is invisible.","recommendation":"Wrap each AI step in its own try/catch or null check. Set a useAi boolean flag to false on any failure and fall through to the non-AI code path. Never surface AI errors to the user on endpoints that have a non-AI fallback.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #11 AI-powered search, WU-004","date":"2026-04-14"}],"tags":["ai","error-handling","fallback","search"],"affectedFiles":["packages/server/src/routes/search.ts"],"affectedServices":["server"],"createdAt":"2026-04-14T15:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-14T15:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
